// External Influence ROI for Staff+ Engineers
// 1 conference talk = artifact for 2 years
// 1 blog post = artifact for 3+ years
// 1 OSS contribution = artifact for entire career
// 1 internal-only project = artifact for 1 quarter
//
// The compounding effect:
// External reputation -> invited to speak -> more reputation
// -> better job opportunities -> stronger negotiation position
// -> more internal influence -> bigger projects -> more to talk about

// Technical Blog Post Template
// Headline: [Problem] — How We Solved [Problem] at [Company]
// Subtitle: Lessons learned, tradeoffs made, and what we'd do differently
// 
// 1. The Problem (2 paragraphs)
//    - What wasn't working
//    - Why it mattered
//    - How we knew it was a problem (data!)
// 
// 2. What We Tried (3-4 paragraphs)
//    - Option A and why it failed
//    - Option B and why it partially worked
//    - Option C and why we chose it
// 
// 3. The Solution (5-8 paragraphs)
//    - Architecture diagram
//    - Key code snippets (no proprietary code)
//    - Metrics before and after
// 
// 4. Tradeoffs & Learnings (2-3 paragraphs)
//    - What we'd do differently
//    - What surprised us
//    - When NOT to use this approach
// 
// 5. Call to action (1 paragraph)
//    - What questions remain
//    - What we're working on next
